00:18:05,431 --> 00:18:10,253
[SPEAKER_11]: You know, we're hearing you'd have to have someone with you to drive the car away or you have to take public transit or a Lyft.

265
00:18:11,813 --> 00:18:15,235
[SPEAKER_11]: You know, that's a pretty significant cost to the person involved.

266
00:18:15,255 --> 00:18:17,436
[SPEAKER_11]: It may not be directed at you, it may be directed at Lyft.

267
00:18:19,477 --> 00:18:19,717
[SPEAKER_11]: You know,

268
00:18:20,622 --> 00:18:30,773
[SPEAKER_11]: Do you provide compensation to the driver for the cost of public transit or do you provide a free lift to allow them to get to the site to access the vehicle?

269
00:18:30,793 --> 00:18:37,220
[SPEAKER_12]: Again, I don't know how that lift side of that works.

270
00:18:37,260 --> 00:18:41,704
[SPEAKER_12]: So unfortunately, I can't answer that either.

271
00:18:41,844 --> 00:18:43,246
[SPEAKER_12]: Christy, are you able to answer that?

272
00:18:45,080 --> 00:18:50,803
[SPEAKER_01]: Yeah, so the, we are not, we don't compensate for the driver coming to the site.

273
00:18:52,203 --> 00:19:03,788
[SPEAKER_01]: It's just like a normal, you know, rental agreement where if they, you know, this is a service that we provide and if it's something that they want to utilize, you know, they come to, they make the appointment and they come to the site.

274
00:19:05,029 --> 00:19:05,309
[SPEAKER_11]: Got it.

275
00:19:06,349 --> 00:19:13,813
[SPEAKER_11]: And then I guess my question there would be to Attorney Blake, would it possible, be possible to put a condition on the permit requiring that

276
00:19:14,985 --> 00:19:22,789
[SPEAKER_11]: either parking be provided for a personal vehicle or compensation be provided to the person for their transit time to the site?

277
00:19:25,270 --> 00:19:33,613
[SPEAKER_08]: I think the former would be a sufficient nexus for this land use permit.

278
00:19:34,234 --> 00:19:37,895
[SPEAKER_08]: I don't think the latter would be requiring compensation.

279
00:19:38,816 --> 00:19:41,417
[SPEAKER_08]: This is a land use permit and there has to be a nexus.

280
00:19:42,039 --> 00:19:56,844
[SPEAKER_08]: obviously having sufficient parking for what could be overflow would have a sufficient and is clearly outlined in your ordinance, the ladder requiring compensation.

281
00:19:57,644 --> 00:20:00,625
[SPEAKER_08]: I think that probably goes beyond what you could do with a land use permit.

282
00:20:02,626 --> 00:20:02,926
[SPEAKER_11]: Got it.

283
00:20:02,946 --> 00:20:03,246
[SPEAKER_11]: Yeah.

284
00:20:03,266 --> 00:20:05,387
[SPEAKER_11]: And I figured you were going to say that, but I just wanted to make sure.

285
00:20:09,690 --> 00:20:34,458
[SPEAKER_11]: I, you know, again, I've voiced my concerns here that, you know, basically we're talking about moving from a business model around providing rides to folks where, you know, you had compensation and capital costs borne by the corporation, now to have compensation and capital costs borne by the worker.

286
00:20:35,375 --> 00:20:40,558
[SPEAKER_11]: and the worker actually has fewer labor protections under the new model than they did under the old model.

287
00:20:41,699 --> 00:20:47,543
[SPEAKER_11]: And, you know, I understand, you know, that's certainly good for profits.

288
00:20:48,664 --> 00:21:01,032
[SPEAKER_11]: It's certainly been good for transit network companies, you know, in the short-term gain of their shareholders, but I seriously question whether it's good for our society and our economy and for people themselves.

289
00:21:02,613 --> 00:21:03,634
[SPEAKER_11]: So at the very least,

290
00:21:04,883 --> 00:21:11,546
[SPEAKER_11]: you know, I'd like to see if we could do the condition that parking be provided for the personal vehicle.

291
00:21:11,626 --> 00:21:20,970
[SPEAKER_11]: That's, it seems like that might be the one thing we can give to the person coming to this site to take a little bit of cost or something off of their plate.

292
00:21:23,691 --> 00:21:26,252
[SPEAKER_11]: So I'll believe that as it is, that's something I'd like to see.

293
00:21:26,312 --> 00:21:26,853
[SPEAKER_11]: I'm not sure.

