312
00:22:20,313 --> 00:22:24,119
[SPEAKER_07]: are not at all what they were a few years ago so I am concerned about.

313
00:22:24,139 --> 00:22:35,435
[SPEAKER_07]: At the same time I'm concerned about drivers I was going to call them employees but they're really more like customers who are coming to the site to use the cars.

314
00:22:37,310 --> 00:22:47,135
[SPEAKER_07]: You know, and making sure that there's a reasonable accommodation for them since they're, you know, paying paying to use the service to pick up to pick up riders.

315
00:22:47,956 --> 00:22:56,880
[SPEAKER_07]: At the same time, if we can only condition the permit for providing parking to drivers, and not compensation for those who are traveling to the site by other means.

316
00:22:57,821 --> 00:23:01,303
[SPEAKER_07]: That strikes me as a bit of an inequitable compensation.

317
00:23:02,400 --> 00:23:11,971
[SPEAKER_07]: mechanism, because we're only conditioning for those who are arriving in personal vehicles and not those who, you know, for example, maybe they don't have access to a personal vehicle, maybe they can't afford one.

318
00:23:12,972 --> 00:23:21,362
[SPEAKER_07]: So I am interested in entertaining that, but it strikes me as kind of only getting at a fraction of the worker population that we're that we're trying to

319
00:23:23,197 --> 00:23:23,858
[SPEAKER_07]: include here.

320
00:23:24,998 --> 00:23:40,649
[SPEAKER_07]: So kind of on both sides of that issue of how are folks getting to this site to use the cars, personal vehicles, public transit, you know, to the extent that some will be driving, pick up the lift vehicles I am interested in seeing that traffic study.

