[SPEAKER_02]: And as you've said, conditions, correct?

344
00:25:36,660 --> 00:25:38,400
[SPEAKER_02]: Because it is land use, it's not about,

345
00:25:39,547 --> 00:25:42,210
[SPEAKER_02]: business organization.

346
00:25:43,451 --> 00:25:44,252
[SPEAKER_08]: That is correct.

347
00:25:44,812 --> 00:25:57,105
[SPEAKER_06]: Are they going to be bringing the cars back to that when they've done, are they going to be bringing the cars back to that location also correct rentals pickups and returns will happen at that location, and will they be like I said,

348
00:25:58,049 --> 00:26:00,770
[SPEAKER_06]: will they be checking into an office or anything, or just drop them off?

349
00:26:00,990 --> 00:26:07,233
[SPEAKER_12]: Yep, so we have the office there, and what we do is we set up appointments on an hourly basis throughout the day, throughout the week, however we need.

350
00:26:07,273 --> 00:26:09,074
[SPEAKER_12]: So they're gonna have to walk across- Drivers make an appointment.

351
00:26:09,214 --> 00:26:14,577
[SPEAKER_06]: They'll have to walk across street to, is there gonna be an office on the station landing side?

352
00:26:14,597 --> 00:26:27,283
[SPEAKER_12]: Yeah, so at the location where the physical location is that we'll be operating out of, the drivers will drop the vehicle at that location, so no crossing of the street, and then Lyft employees will bring those vehicles to that side separate lot.

353
00:26:29,875 --> 00:26:31,656
[SPEAKER_12]: employees are the ones on site.

354
00:26:34,557 --> 00:26:35,978
[SPEAKER_02]: Christie Lawrence, I saw you had your hand up.

355
00:26:38,539 --> 00:26:39,099
[SPEAKER_01]: I did, yeah.

356
00:26:39,179 --> 00:26:56,526
[SPEAKER_01]: One of the things that I just wanted to bring up too is we have done traffic studies in the past for other markets and just one thing to bring up is our peak times tend to be between noon and 3 o'clock and usually it tends, I mean even more so it's been around 145 to 245.

357
00:26:58,970 --> 00:27:05,754
[SPEAKER_01]: So I just wanted to call that out because our drivers want to be out on the market, you know, want to be out driving during peak times.

358
00:27:06,354 --> 00:27:11,477
[SPEAKER_01]: And so from a traffic perspective, really the in and out happens in the middle of the day.

359
00:27:12,358 --> 00:27:15,399
[SPEAKER_01]: Just something that I wanted to call out from a traffic perspective.

360
00:27:15,419 --> 00:27:16,940
[SPEAKER_02]: I appreciate that.

361
00:27:16,960 --> 00:27:19,722
[SPEAKER_02]: Have you have you been to the space where this would be operating from?

