00:30:53,076 --> 00:30:53,696
[SPEAKER_02]: Councilor Carvilla.

394
00:30:54,276 --> 00:30:56,917
[SPEAKER_06]: For those who know, these people are classified as independent contractors.

395
00:30:57,878 --> 00:30:58,978
[SPEAKER_06]: They don't get an hourly wage.

396
00:30:59,678 --> 00:31:00,518
[SPEAKER_06]: Misclassified.

397
00:31:01,219 --> 00:31:05,700
[SPEAKER_06]: Well, they're classified as independent contractors.

398
00:31:05,720 --> 00:31:09,121
[SPEAKER_06]: So they're not getting any health insurance or any benefits from the company.

399
00:31:10,757 --> 00:31:21,859
[SPEAKER_06]: For those who don't know, City of Medford derives, I think, 20 cents for every ride share service that starts in Medford.

400
00:31:21,879 --> 00:31:25,900
[SPEAKER_06]: And you'd be surprised how many that do start in Medford.

401
00:31:25,980 --> 00:31:30,881
[SPEAKER_06]: I think last year we had a couple hundred thousand.

402
00:31:31,321 --> 00:31:34,982
[SPEAKER_06]: And those cards that they're taking aren't necessarily gonna be in Medford.

403
00:31:35,022 --> 00:31:39,283
[SPEAKER_06]: If they happen to get calls in Medford, then they do, but they're made to go anywhere they want.

404
00:31:39,959 --> 00:31:44,663
[SPEAKER_06]: Some of them will be doing food deliveries, am I correct?

405
00:31:44,703 --> 00:31:45,604
[SPEAKER_06]: Like, you know, Grubhub.

406
00:31:45,664 --> 00:31:48,526
[SPEAKER_06]: And they can use anything they want.

407
00:31:48,546 --> 00:31:55,011
[SPEAKER_06]: So these people, they're independent contractors and they have to really scramble to make their money.

408
00:31:55,632 --> 00:32:07,141
